                  </persName>
            . I lodge in <placeName id="t17750426-78-crimeloc385">Swan Alley London Wall</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17750426-78-crimeloc385" type="placeName" value="Swan Alley London Wall"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17750426-78-crimeloc385" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17750426-78-off383 t17750426-78-crimeloc385"></join>, my things were lost out of my box in the night of the 7th of march, I saw them in my box at eleven at night when I went to bed, the box was locked, but it was a very bad lock; in the morning the lid of the box was lying on the floor, and the things were gone, the prisoner used to be with me; not coming home all that night to my knowledge, nor to work the next morning, I suspected him, I informed my brother of it and he went to Justice Wilmot, and got one of his men to go in search of the prisoner, when he was taken he confessed the fact, when I was present. I found my things at the pawnbrokers in consequence of his direction.</p>
               <p>
            
