            , a pawn-broker produced a coat, a waistcoat, a pair of breeches and two old shirts, which he received of the prisoner, on the 8th of March.</p>
               <p>- Fox a pawnbroker produced a great coat, which he deposed he received of the prisoner on the 8th of March: They were deposed to by the prosecutor.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I worked for the prosecutor, he was short of money, he gave me leave to take them out of the box to pawn, to raise some money to buy tools (this the prosecutor denied.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner called two witnesses who gave him a good character.</p>
